import { SvgIcon } from '@mui/material';

function Logo() {
  return (
    <SvgIcon sx={{ fontSize: 32, mr: 1 }}>
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 100 100">
        <defs>
          <linearGradient id="goldGradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
            <stop offset="0%" style={{ stopColor: '#FFD700' }} />
            <stop offset="100%" style={{ stopColor: '#DAA520' }} />
          </linearGradient>
        </defs>
        <g transform="translate(20, 15)">
          <path
            d="M30 0 C45 0, 60 15, 60 30 C60 45, 45 60, 30 60 C15 60, 0 45, 0 30 C0 15, 15 0, 30 0 M30 10 C40 10, 50 20, 50 30 C50 40, 40 50, 30 50 C20 50, 10 40, 10 30 C10 20, 20 10, 30 10"
            fill="url(#goldGradient)"
          />
          <path
            d="M15 25 L45 25 M15 35 L45 35"
            stroke="url(#goldGradient)"
            strokeWidth="3"
            fill="none"
          />
          <circle cx="30" cy="30" r="3" fill="url(#goldGradient)" />
          <path
            d="M30 5 L30 15 M30 45 L30 55"
            stroke="url(#goldGradient)"
            strokeWidth="3"
            fill="none"
          />
        </g>
      </svg>
    </SvgIcon>
  );
}

export default Logo;
